1
00:00:00,087 --> 00:00:01,693
I want to marry North.

2
00:00:02,481 --> 00:00:03,983
Will you give me another chance?

3
00:00:04,409 --> 00:00:06,996
I promise to take good care of you.

4
00:00:07,695 --> 00:00:09,141
I talked to your Grandpa today.

5
00:00:09,233 --> 00:00:11,400
He told me
to introduce my family to yours.

6
00:00:12,029 --> 00:00:15,600
Tim has been proving to us
that he loves my grandson.

7
00:00:15,827 --> 00:00:17,815
I’m willing to spend my whole life
proving myself to you.

8
00:00:18,563 --> 00:00:20,613
I’ll give you another chance.

9
00:00:21,866 --> 00:00:23,200
Let’s get back together.

10
00:00:30,918 --> 00:00:34,130
U’s mother can not be here today
to ask for North’s hand in marriage.

11
00:00:34,381 --> 00:00:37,181
So allow me to represent U in this regard

12
00:00:41,473 --> 00:00:44,300
I don’t actually mind.

13
00:00:45,420 --> 00:00:46,598
Which means I do.

14
00:00:51,830 --> 00:00:56,460
But I want to see you happy
with the person you chose, North.

15
00:00:56,910 --> 00:00:59,340
Grandpa. You scared me.

16
00:01:00,300 --> 00:01:04,823
I have been watching you all
since you started working at Empire.

17
00:01:04,980 --> 00:01:07,738
I’ve been watching
how much you’ve all grown.

18
00:01:08,580 --> 00:01:09,740
Alright.

19
00:01:10,503 --> 00:01:17,740
I give you my blessing and hope
your marriage is always full of happiness.

20
00:01:18,212 --> 00:01:19,743
Thank you, Grandpa.

21
00:01:20,181 --> 00:01:21,013
Thank you, sir.

22
00:01:23,029 --> 00:01:24,303
I’ll leave him in your care.

23
00:01:24,561 --> 00:01:29,663
If I ever see my grandson cry, get sad,
or disappointed because of you…

24
00:01:32,050 --> 00:01:34,403
I’ll make sure you don’t spend
another peaceful day in your life.

25
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:46,098
I’m joking.

26
00:01:46,412 --> 00:01:47,738
I wouldn’t do that.

27
00:01:49,073 --> 00:01:50,261
You definitely wouldn’t!

28
00:01:51,510 --> 00:01:52,804
I mean, I could.

29
00:01:53,021 --> 00:01:53,863
But I wouldn’t.

30
00:01:55,210 --> 00:01:56,733
Of course not.

31
00:01:57,369 --> 00:01:58,300
Same goes to you, Tim.
Sir?

32
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:00,735
Watch your back.

33
00:02:05,567 --> 00:02:07,253
Grandpa, you really have a sense of humor!

34
00:02:07,269 --> 00:02:09,100
You’re scaring him!

35
00:02:15,490 --> 00:02:17,301
Are you going to the office, Pai?

36
00:02:17,380 --> 00:02:19,338
Wanna hop on? We can give you a lift.

37
00:02:19,633 --> 00:02:20,332
It’s okay.

38
00:02:20,786 --> 00:02:23,001
I’m getting to know Tim’s friend today.

39
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:24,704
You can go ahead and go to work, North.

40
00:02:25,310 --> 00:02:26,600
You have a friend now?

41
00:02:27,050 --> 00:02:29,100
He’s a thief.
You wanna get to know him, too?

42
00:02:31,789 --> 00:02:32,800
Maybe not.

43
00:02:32,890 --> 00:02:35,946
But before I go, can I ask you something?

44
00:02:39,007 --> 00:02:42,175
Thank you for representing U’s side
of the family today, Pai.

45
00:02:43,350 --> 00:02:44,180
I love you.

46
00:02:44,675 --> 00:02:45,700
Thank you, Pai—

47
00:02:45,720 --> 00:02:46,803
Hold it right there.

48
00:02:47,130 --> 00:02:49,298
What do you think you’re doing?
Don’t even think about it.

49
00:02:49,527 --> 00:02:50,580
-Stay back.
-Okay.

50
00:02:50,713 --> 00:02:52,740
I was just giving him
a grateful embrace, though.

51
00:02:52,770 --> 00:02:53,903
It’s nothing to worry about.

52
00:02:54,040 --> 00:02:55,100
Don’t be so dramatic.

53
00:02:57,472 --> 00:02:58,530
I’ll let it slip this time.

54
00:02:58,750 --> 00:02:59,803
Don’t be so dramatic.

55
00:03:08,203 --> 00:03:09,981
Cheeky, aren’t you?

56
00:03:10,364 --> 00:03:11,981
Go. Go away.

57
00:03:13,493 --> 00:03:14,903
Anyone ever told you
you’re the jealous type?

58
00:03:14,933 --> 00:03:16,056
How can I not be?

59
00:03:16,813 --> 00:03:18,101
Look at my boyfriend.

60
00:03:18,133 --> 00:03:20,298
I nearly died trying to win him back.

61
00:03:21,490 --> 00:03:23,298
I’m off, then. See you, Pai.

62
00:03:25,121 --> 00:03:26,196
This way, sir.

63
00:03:40,532 --> 00:03:42,129
It’s getting hot, U.

64
00:03:42,155 --> 00:03:42,900
Okay.

65
00:03:45,020 --> 00:03:46,403
-Drive safe.
-Of course.

66
00:03:46,567 --> 00:03:47,704
Slow down.

67
00:03:48,269 --> 00:03:49,400
I can’t help it!

68
00:03:52,624 --> 00:03:53,340
Baby.

69
00:03:54,870 --> 00:03:56,343
Don’t you want to give me a hug, too?

70
00:03:57,876 --> 00:03:58,901
Fine, fine.

71
00:04:01,570 --> 00:04:02,304
Hey.

72
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:03,996
Hugs only.

73
00:04:21,330 --> 00:04:22,350
Hello, Pai.

74
00:04:24,730 --> 00:04:26,381
I guess our first impression
wasn’t very nice.

75
00:04:26,650 --> 00:04:29,198
But let me reintroduce myself.

76
00:04:30,560 --> 00:04:31,404
My name is Prem.

77
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:33,981
I’m Tim’s only friend.

78
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:50,098
How did you guys even know
each other anyway?

79
00:05:15,704 --> 00:05:16,620
Is something wrong?

80
00:05:17,867 --> 00:05:19,503
No.

81
00:05:22,020 --> 00:05:22,801
All done.

82
00:05:25,413 --> 00:05:26,200
Thank you.

83
00:06:49,049 --> 00:06:49,701
Da Zhan?

84
00:06:53,806 --> 00:06:55,735
What do you mean
you’re leaving Da Zhan in my care?

85
00:06:56,070 --> 00:06:58,181
I’ve been super busy lately.

86
00:06:58,901 --> 00:07:02,236
I’m flying to our branch in London soon.

87
00:07:02,576 --> 00:07:04,701
(I just can’t leave Da Zhan alone.)

88
00:07:04,860 --> 00:07:07,053
But I doubt Da Zhan
would want to spend time with me.

89
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:08,380
I’d love to.

90
00:07:09,067 --> 00:07:09,798
What?

91
00:07:13,261 --> 00:07:14,504
Why me?

92
00:07:14,592 --> 00:07:15,946
(Besides you,)

93
00:07:16,090 --> 00:07:18,307
there is no one else I can trust.

94
00:07:19,460 --> 00:07:23,343
Oh, don’t forget North has to meet up
with our Master at Grandpa’s today.

95
00:07:23,503 --> 00:07:26,158
After that,
drop Da Zhan off at his school,

96
00:07:26,186 --> 00:07:27,610
and pick him up in the afternoon.

97
00:07:27,860 --> 00:07:30,100
(I trust you’ll take good care of
your younger cousins.)

98
00:07:30,132 --> 00:07:31,203
(I have to go.)

99
00:07:31,764 --> 00:07:32,935
(Oh, hold on.)

100
00:07:33,190 --> 00:07:35,284
Let me know if you want anything
from London, Pai.

101
00:07:35,301 --> 00:07:36,201
I’ll buy them for you.

102
00:07:36,460 --> 00:07:37,403
Of course.

103
00:07:37,876 --> 00:07:39,000
Thank you, Auntie.

104
00:07:45,221 --> 00:07:45,860
Pai.

105
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:46,863
I’m hungry.

106
00:07:51,769 --> 00:07:54,261
Are our fortunes compatible, Master?

107
00:07:57,932 --> 00:07:59,580
From your birth charts,

108
00:08:00,224 --> 00:08:02,896
it wasn’t likely
for the two of you to meet.

109
00:08:02,984 --> 00:08:06,698
But now that you’re together,
your fortunes are bolstering each other.

110
00:08:06,886 --> 00:08:08,741
All in all, it’s superb.

111
00:08:09,746 --> 00:08:10,740
That’s good.

112
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:14,856
As for the best time for your wedding…

113
00:08:17,180 --> 00:08:18,995
It’ll need to be a day
with the element of water.

114
00:08:19,053 --> 00:08:21,536
There’s a few days like that soon.

115
00:08:22,481 --> 00:08:23,212
Right.

116
00:08:30,790 --> 00:08:33,000
Just ask me
what you’re thinking about asking.

117
00:08:35,713 --> 00:08:37,101
Is it about that man?

118
00:08:38,141 --> 00:08:39,781
The one you were married to?

119
00:08:40,524 --> 00:08:41,204
Yes.

120
00:08:42,203 --> 00:08:44,138
I told you not to rush into it.

121
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:46,341
Your timing has come and passed.

122
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:47,749
Sorry?

123
00:08:48,796 --> 00:08:51,223
The stake is very high this time.

124
00:08:51,338 --> 00:08:54,400
If you are victorious in this,
the reward is twice as sweet.

125
00:08:54,681 --> 00:08:58,093
The present is the best time.

126
00:08:58,301 --> 00:09:03,255
One move could shake things up
or tear it all down.

127
00:09:04,075 --> 00:09:05,498
What does that mean, sir?

128
00:09:05,795 --> 00:09:07,696
He knows well what this means.

129
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:11,603
Marrying him could simply break even
or make it worse.

130
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:12,500
Right.

131
00:09:13,450 --> 00:09:15,700
I’m not thinking
about getting married right now anyway.

132
00:09:28,372 --> 00:09:30,369
That was pretty accurate, wasn’t it?

133
00:09:30,744 --> 00:09:31,600
It was.

134
00:09:40,156 --> 00:09:40,893
Pai.

135
00:09:42,930 --> 00:09:43,692
Pai!

136
00:09:44,790 --> 00:09:45,440
Yes?

137
00:09:45,940 --> 00:09:47,903
Are you worried
about what the Master said?

138
00:09:49,949 --> 00:09:50,703
No.

139
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:52,380
I’m never a believer, you know.

140
00:10:00,207 --> 00:10:01,416
Yeah, I am worried.

141
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:04,304
But I’m already intending
to take things slow with Tim.

142
00:10:04,521 --> 00:10:06,026
If we ever want to get married,

143
00:10:06,060 --> 00:10:07,495
it wouldn’t be any time soon.

144
00:10:08,827 --> 00:10:10,780
Don’t tell Tim
this for now, though, North.

145
00:10:19,226 --> 00:10:21,420
You wouldn’t tell anyone,
would you, Da Zhan?

146
00:10:23,547 --> 00:10:24,601
Would you, Da Zhan?

147
00:10:29,833 --> 00:10:31,700
I have to drop Da Zhan off at school.

148
00:10:33,646 --> 00:10:35,903
I have a signing class after this as well.

149
00:10:37,712 --> 00:10:38,653
Singing class?

150
00:10:39,400 --> 00:10:44,815
♪ For someone to find someone ♪

151
00:10:45,001 --> 00:10:49,198
♪ What could the reason be ♪

152
00:10:53,616 --> 00:10:54,400
Ma’am?

153
00:10:57,126 --> 00:10:57,796
Right.

154
00:10:58,630 --> 00:11:00,620
It was so good she had to step away
to appreciate the song.

155
00:11:00,780 --> 00:11:02,300
What do you think about dancing?

156
00:11:02,549 --> 00:11:03,800
…What about singing?

157
00:11:04,463 --> 00:11:05,501
Maybe dancing is better.

158
00:11:08,715 --> 00:11:10,415
…Six, seven, go.

159
00:11:17,852 --> 00:11:18,500
Ouch!
Oh?

160
00:11:19,420 --> 00:11:20,098
North?

161
00:11:21,292 --> 00:11:21,996
Are you alright?

162
00:11:24,889 --> 00:11:26,133
North!

163
00:11:26,706 --> 00:11:28,396
Owww!

164
00:11:30,227 --> 00:11:31,930
It hurts.

165
00:11:32,013 --> 00:11:33,003
Alright.

166
00:11:34,480 --> 00:11:35,396
How does that feel?

167
00:11:39,096 --> 00:11:42,416
I guess performance is a no-no.

168
00:11:43,140 --> 00:11:45,381
I think we’ll be going places
with some more practice.

169
00:11:45,495 --> 00:11:47,589
The only place we’re going
is the emergency room.

170
00:11:49,201 --> 00:11:50,300
It’s too bad.

171
00:11:50,558 --> 00:11:52,996
I’d love to put on a performance
for the guests.

172
00:11:53,483 --> 00:11:55,298
It’s the wedding of a top business tycoon.

173
00:11:55,590 --> 00:11:57,001
I don’t want to disappoint anyone.

174
00:11:57,498 --> 00:11:58,798
Oh, North.

175
00:11:59,230 --> 00:12:01,001
Don’t put such a pressure
on yourself like that.

176
00:12:01,110 --> 00:12:04,430
I think we should just do what we want.

177
00:12:04,476 --> 00:12:05,603
Do what we enjoy.

178
00:12:05,970 --> 00:12:07,298
It’s our wedding, you know?

179
00:12:07,410 --> 00:12:09,336
We should prioritize our own needs.

180
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:10,338
Right?

181
00:12:15,589 --> 00:12:16,893
Oh, it hurts.

182
00:12:17,221 --> 00:12:18,603
-It hurts.
-Your head?

183
00:12:19,546 --> 00:12:20,701
Here. Take this.

184
00:12:24,375 --> 00:12:25,296
Pai, hello.

185
00:12:26,238 --> 00:12:26,998
Hello.

186
00:12:35,289 --> 00:12:37,530
Even though I haven’t been
taking care of this place for a while,

187
00:12:37,556 --> 00:12:38,972
but I think the numbers
are still pretty good.

188
00:12:39,016 --> 00:12:41,500
I’ll even say
you’re doing a good job, Pure.

189
00:12:42,692 --> 00:12:43,500
Of course.

190
00:12:47,270 --> 00:12:48,153
Wow.

191
00:12:48,649 --> 00:12:50,900
You look like a prince, like a royal.

192
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:54,796
What brought you to my humble bakery,
Your Highness?

193
00:12:55,338 --> 00:12:56,295
Quit it, dude.

194
00:12:56,860 --> 00:12:58,400
Where are you going
all dressed up like that?

195
00:12:58,547 --> 00:13:00,903
Ms. Nana said U and I
have to attend an event.

196
00:13:02,760 --> 00:13:03,950
And where is U?

197
00:13:04,240 --> 00:13:06,652
He said he needed to get his fill
of some good food before he goes.

198
00:13:06,690 --> 00:13:08,540
He thinks the food at the event
might not be good.

199
00:13:14,636 --> 00:13:15,704
What’s wrong?

200
00:13:20,896 --> 00:13:21,700
Well…

201
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:25,780
It’s the wedding. I’m tired.

202
00:13:26,578 --> 00:13:28,600
It’s just too much.

203
00:13:29,273 --> 00:13:32,456
This is the answer guide
for the interview at the wedding.

204
00:13:32,578 --> 00:13:35,541
You can find Mr. U’s profile
and your first encounter here.

205
00:13:35,572 --> 00:13:39,416
The entire script has been approved
by your Grandpa and our legal team.

206
00:13:39,921 --> 00:13:41,096
Script?

207
00:13:41,206 --> 00:13:41,904
Yes.

208
00:13:45,380 --> 00:13:47,204
Oh, dear, North.

209
00:13:55,520 --> 00:13:56,181
Pai.

210
00:13:58,010 --> 00:13:59,403
Why don’t we just get married
on the same day?

211
00:14:03,769 --> 00:14:04,903
I told you…

212
00:14:05,230 --> 00:14:06,518
I’m not thinking about marriage right now.

213
00:14:06,600 --> 00:14:08,300
Are you really not thinking about it,

214
00:14:08,973 --> 00:14:10,695
or are you just afraid
of what the Master said?

215
00:14:10,729 --> 00:14:12,744
You don’t have to believe
everything he says.

216
00:14:12,773 --> 00:14:14,504
Sometimes he’s just sprouting nonsense.

217
00:14:14,976 --> 00:14:16,261
I don’t believe him.

218
00:14:16,481 --> 00:14:18,260
The Master said something?
What did he say?

219
00:14:18,564 --> 00:14:22,695
He said Pai and Tim’s timing
has come and passed.

220
00:14:23,470 --> 00:14:25,778
But I’ll be honest. I think it’s nonsense.

221
00:14:27,109 --> 00:14:28,423
You said you believed him
just this morning.

222
00:14:28,612 --> 00:14:29,296
Oh?

223
00:14:31,646 --> 00:14:33,410
I mean, I believe the good things.

224
00:14:33,704 --> 00:14:36,801
It doesn’t mean I have to believe
the bad things, you know?

225
00:14:38,229 --> 00:14:39,060
Can you do that?

226
00:14:40,906 --> 00:14:42,740
I’ve been sticking to that principle
my whole life.

227
00:14:45,180 --> 00:14:46,426
Come on, Pai.

228
00:14:46,455 --> 00:14:47,415
Please, please, please.

229
00:14:47,872 --> 00:14:49,184
Just think about it.

230
00:14:49,340 --> 00:14:53,098
If it’s not auspicious,
I’m sure the Master has a solution for it.

231
00:14:56,260 --> 00:14:57,081
What are you guys talking about?

232
00:14:57,130 --> 00:14:59,540
-Nothing!
-We are not talking at all!

233
00:15:00,038 --> 00:15:02,415
I’d better go home.

234
00:15:02,489 --> 00:15:03,489
Da Zhan, come on.

235
00:15:03,516 --> 00:15:04,195
Let’s go home.
Yes.

236
00:15:04,969 --> 00:15:06,198
Be nice and listen to Pai.

237
00:15:09,238 --> 00:15:09,903
Let’s go.

238
00:15:12,404 --> 00:15:14,378
Were you guys talking behind my back
or something?

239
00:15:14,504 --> 00:15:16,146
-Of course not!
-Clearly not!

240
00:15:16,167 --> 00:15:16,898
Not at all!

241
00:15:16,920 --> 00:15:19,138
-Who’d do something like that?
-He’s right.

242
00:15:39,780 --> 00:15:40,700
Da Zhan.

243
00:15:42,620 --> 00:15:44,463
Why don’t you have dinner
before you play your game?

244
00:15:47,927 --> 00:15:48,798
Sure.

245
00:15:55,086 --> 00:15:57,376
I’ll draw a warm bath for you.

246
00:16:07,058 --> 00:16:08,801
You guys kiss?

247
00:16:11,675 --> 00:16:12,424
No.

248
00:16:12,970 --> 00:16:14,018
Just have your dinner.

249
00:16:41,095 --> 00:16:41,980
Is something wrong?

250
00:16:44,818 --> 00:16:45,424
No.

251
00:17:11,335 --> 00:17:13,101
Alright!

252
00:17:13,238 --> 00:17:14,903
See that? Aren’t I amazing?

253
00:17:15,706 --> 00:17:17,295
How can I even pull this off?

254
00:17:17,360 --> 00:17:18,380
Oh, Pai.

255
00:17:18,493 --> 00:17:19,373
Come and play.

256
00:17:21,453 --> 00:17:22,381
Come on, Pai.

257
00:17:22,409 --> 00:17:24,001
Just come on here and play.

258
00:17:25,090 --> 00:17:26,503
Let’s play with Da Zhan.

259
00:17:27,946 --> 00:17:28,616
Alright.

260
00:17:29,816 --> 00:17:31,801
It’s Pai’s turn.

261
00:17:31,833 --> 00:17:32,612
Alright.

262
00:17:40,147 --> 00:17:41,856
Be careful, Pai.

263
00:17:42,633 --> 00:17:44,796
The stake is high, you know?

264
00:17:47,135 --> 00:17:50,652
(The present is the best time.)

265
00:17:50,866 --> 00:17:56,201
One move could shake things up
or tear it all down.

266
00:18:23,484 --> 00:18:25,396
We kept it standing for so long, you know?

267
00:18:25,590 --> 00:18:26,415
I’m sorry.

268
00:18:27,110 --> 00:18:29,892
Da Zhan, since it’s game over,
why don’t you go and take a shower?

269
00:18:31,404 --> 00:18:32,420
Can’t we play one more game?

270
00:18:32,450 --> 00:18:34,198
We can play later. Go take a shower.

271
00:18:34,396 --> 00:18:35,803
Let’s go. I’ll walk with you.

272
00:18:36,823 --> 00:18:38,398
Alright. Pack it up.

273
00:18:39,321 --> 00:18:40,201
Let’s go.

274
00:18:41,967 --> 00:18:44,401
Go, go, go, go.

275
00:18:45,466 --> 00:18:46,503
Right in there.

276
00:18:48,290 --> 00:18:49,303
Good job.

277
00:19:27,320 --> 00:19:28,201
Easy.

278
00:19:28,735 --> 00:19:29,896
Take it slow.

279
00:19:30,503 --> 00:19:32,003
I don’t want to get married.

280
00:19:32,140 --> 00:19:33,740
I don’t want to start a family.

281
00:19:34,436 --> 00:19:35,898
I don’t like what happened today.

282
00:19:40,410 --> 00:19:42,204
Is everything alright?

283
00:19:44,376 --> 00:19:45,500
When did you get here?

284
00:19:46,180 --> 00:19:47,150
Did you hear anything?

285
00:19:48,229 --> 00:19:49,000
Oh

286
00:19:49,587 --> 00:19:50,267
No.

287
00:19:51,080 --> 00:19:52,396
I didn’t.

288
00:19:54,443 --> 00:19:56,000
Ugh!

289
00:19:57,238 --> 00:19:59,496
That was tiring.

290
00:19:59,687 --> 00:20:01,900
If we had to go through that
every time we’re at an event,

291
00:20:02,186 --> 00:20:03,498
what would we do?

292
00:20:07,401 --> 00:20:09,400
I don’t want to get married anymore.

293
00:20:10,350 --> 00:20:11,000
What?

294
00:20:13,706 --> 00:20:14,378
North.

295
00:20:15,549 --> 00:20:16,200
North.

296
00:20:19,660 --> 00:20:20,649
He’s just sleeptalking.

297
00:20:22,990 --> 00:20:24,198
What did I do?

298
00:20:24,446 --> 00:20:26,898
Pai suddenly panics
and doesn’t want to marry me.

299
00:20:27,083 --> 00:20:28,441
I was only thinking about it.

300
00:20:28,476 --> 00:20:29,496
I haven’t even said anything.

301
00:20:29,629 --> 00:20:31,898
Did Pai tell you
about what the Master said?

302
00:20:34,507 --> 00:20:35,263
What did he say?

303
00:20:35,456 --> 00:20:37,824
He said you shouldn’t get married
because your timing has gone by,

304
00:20:37,850 --> 00:20:39,783
and that it would be unauspicious
if you get married.

305
00:20:40,358 --> 00:20:42,063
Master is a nosy bastard!

306
00:20:42,172 --> 00:20:43,801
I want to marry him!

307
00:20:44,035 --> 00:20:45,053
What do I do now?

308
00:20:45,350 --> 00:20:46,373
Break up with him?

309
00:20:46,531 --> 00:20:47,305
Right?

310
00:20:47,540 --> 00:20:48,896
I want to get married, too.

311
00:20:49,183 --> 00:20:50,998
But then North said
he doesn’t want to anymore.

312
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:54,502
Now I don’t even know if we’re still on
for our pre-wedding photoshoot next week.

313
00:20:57,779 --> 00:20:59,539
Maybe I shouldn’t ask Pai to marry me?

314
00:21:04,860 --> 00:21:05,601
Hey.

315
00:21:06,054 --> 00:21:07,096
You busy tomorrow?

316
00:21:07,820 --> 00:21:08,998
Let’s have dinner at my place.

317
00:21:09,496 --> 00:21:10,697
Bring North.

318
00:21:10,930 --> 00:21:13,540
I want to throw a little party
before I sell that house.

319
00:21:13,758 --> 00:21:15,379
Oh, you have a buyer?

320
00:21:18,130 --> 00:21:18,900
Alright.

321
00:21:20,231 --> 00:21:21,000
But…

322
00:21:21,640 --> 00:21:23,651
What will you do about Pai?

323
00:21:26,790 --> 00:21:29,099
If he doesn’t want to marry me,
what can I even do?

324
00:21:40,933 --> 00:21:42,023
Tim, hello.

325
00:21:42,183 --> 00:21:43,379
Hey.

326
00:21:43,410 --> 00:21:44,197
Hey there.

327
00:21:44,560 --> 00:21:46,297
This is from U and I.

328
00:21:47,521 --> 00:21:48,720
-Thank you.
-Sure.

329
00:21:48,902 --> 00:21:49,502
Here.

330
00:21:49,906 --> 00:21:50,942
I’ll put it away.

331
00:21:52,598 --> 00:21:53,300
Thank you.

332
00:22:00,925 --> 00:22:01,694
Oh, Pai.

333
00:22:01,720 --> 00:22:04,496
Why don’t you come and help me
with the tablecloth?

334
00:22:05,790 --> 00:22:07,097
Uhh, how about…

335
00:22:08,032 --> 00:22:08,971
Are you guys fighting?

336
00:22:12,900 --> 00:22:13,851
Not really.

337
00:22:14,660 --> 00:22:16,502
I might have made Tim mad.

338
00:22:17,280 --> 00:22:18,337
What did you do?

339
00:22:18,730 --> 00:22:20,801
I was talking to myself
about not wanting to get married.

340
00:22:21,562 --> 00:22:23,823
Tim must have heard it but said he didn’t.

341
00:22:24,816 --> 00:22:26,696
But why don’t you talk to him?

342
00:22:27,410 --> 00:22:28,897
What can I even tell him?

343
00:22:29,342 --> 00:22:32,900
I really said what I said.

344
00:22:42,040 --> 00:22:46,802
But if Tim wants to marry you,
won’t you even consider it?

345
00:22:53,022 --> 00:22:53,665
Hey.
Yeah?

346
00:22:54,650 --> 00:22:55,853
You guys haven’t talked?

347
00:22:56,970 --> 00:22:58,290
What is there to talk about?

348
00:22:58,850 --> 00:23:00,601
All I can do is put up with it, right?

349
00:23:14,650 --> 00:23:15,303
North.

350
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:16,896
What are you doing?

351
00:23:18,477 --> 00:23:19,699
It’s a new way of stretching.

352
00:23:20,339 --> 00:23:21,340
Stretch, you know.

353
00:23:32,008 --> 00:23:32,798
Uhh…

354
00:23:33,863 --> 00:23:38,054
Tim and Pai, how are you two doing?

355
00:23:42,730 --> 00:23:45,496
Now that you’re back together,
you’re just like a newlywed.

356
00:23:45,786 --> 00:23:46,361
Right?

357
00:23:46,386 --> 00:23:47,499
Newlywed?

358
00:23:47,950 --> 00:23:49,801
I haven’t thought about that
in a long time.

359
00:23:53,826 --> 00:23:55,777
True! It’s too much trouble.

360
00:23:56,081 --> 00:23:57,202
Who’d want to get married?

361
00:23:57,705 --> 00:23:58,294
True!

362
00:23:58,349 --> 00:24:00,081
Getting married is just
getting your family into trouble.

363
00:24:00,109 --> 00:24:01,204
Who’d want that?

364
00:24:02,557 --> 00:24:03,297
Ugh!

365
00:24:04,792 --> 00:24:05,700
I’ve had it!

366
00:24:06,154 --> 00:24:07,102
North, sit down.

367
00:24:09,850 --> 00:24:11,899
Why don’t you just talk it out?

368
00:24:14,632 --> 00:24:15,300
He’s right.

369
00:24:15,656 --> 00:24:18,100
Why can’t you two just talk?

370
00:24:19,259 --> 00:24:21,160
I… I don’t—

371
00:24:21,365 --> 00:24:22,171
-You do!
-You do!

372
00:24:22,250 --> 00:24:24,260
Stop lying to yourselves!

373
00:24:24,404 --> 00:24:27,160
I’ve been rooting for you two
to get back together.

374
00:24:27,191 --> 00:24:28,299
Only for this to happen?

375
00:24:28,370 --> 00:24:29,417
What a headache!

376
00:24:29,570 --> 00:24:30,780
Just keep quiet, U.

377
00:24:31,194 --> 00:24:31,998
U!

378
00:24:32,549 --> 00:24:33,700
Do not keep quiet!

379
00:24:34,312 --> 00:24:37,539
And both of you
shouldn’t keep quiet, either!

380
00:24:38,056 --> 00:24:38,550
He’s right.

381
00:24:38,574 --> 00:24:40,503
You can’t even solve
this little matter on your own?

382
00:24:40,971 --> 00:24:41,888
I don’t get it.

383
00:24:42,900 --> 00:24:44,773
What about you? Did you talk to North?

384
00:24:48,350 --> 00:24:50,000
Talk to me about what? What is it?

385
00:24:51,800 --> 00:24:53,343
-It’s nothing.
-What is it?

386
00:24:53,380 --> 00:24:54,800
I’ll talk to him at home.

387
00:24:55,081 --> 00:24:56,195
Let’s go home, North.

388
00:24:56,903 --> 00:24:57,602
U!

389
00:24:57,939 --> 00:24:59,266
We’ll talk here.

390
00:24:59,804 --> 00:25:01,001
What did you do?

391
00:25:02,370 --> 00:25:03,490
Go ahead and talk to him.

392
00:25:03,573 --> 00:25:04,395
Go on.

393
00:25:05,440 --> 00:25:06,202
No!

394
00:25:09,063 --> 00:25:09,936
U!

395
00:25:31,351 --> 00:25:32,020
U.

396
00:25:34,357 --> 00:25:36,302
What does Tim mean by what he said?

397
00:25:41,558 --> 00:25:43,401
It’s…

398
00:25:44,442 --> 00:25:47,102
The other day, you were sleeptalking.

399
00:25:47,506 --> 00:25:49,779
You said you didn’t want to marry me.

400
00:25:52,223 --> 00:25:53,497
Oh, that.

401
00:25:56,075 --> 00:25:57,980
So what is it?

402
00:25:58,296 --> 00:26:01,200
I wasn’t sleeptalking.

403
00:26:01,660 --> 00:26:05,502
I was just complaining
that I don’t want to get married anymore.

404
00:26:06,354 --> 00:26:07,000
What?

405
00:26:07,176 --> 00:26:08,903
But that’s not what I meant!

406
00:26:10,100 --> 00:26:14,699
I meant, I don’t want to lie to people
and wear a mask all through the ceremony.

407
00:26:15,680 --> 00:26:17,601
I don’t want our wedding to be like that.

408
00:26:21,882 --> 00:26:23,343
Do you understand?

409
00:26:28,750 --> 00:26:30,395
Did you overthink?

410
00:26:32,850 --> 00:26:33,601
I did.

411
00:26:34,480 --> 00:26:35,600
Big time.

412
00:26:37,656 --> 00:26:39,814
It’s not like that. Don’t worry about it.

413
00:26:41,760 --> 00:26:43,201
Alright. Let’s get inside.

414
00:27:02,920 --> 00:27:03,645
Pai.

415
00:27:04,641 --> 00:27:05,819
Can I ask you something?

416
00:27:07,687 --> 00:27:09,600
If you don’t want to get married,

417
00:27:10,730 --> 00:27:12,297
or start a family,

418
00:27:14,130 --> 00:27:17,302
then what kind of idea do you have for us?

419
00:27:18,194 --> 00:27:19,300
That’s not the case.

420
00:27:22,990 --> 00:27:24,822
Are you worried
about what the Master said?

421
00:27:26,746 --> 00:27:29,595
I’m not a believer and you know it.

422
00:27:30,721 --> 00:27:31,600
But…

423
00:27:32,480 --> 00:27:34,302
He had a point.

424
00:27:37,454 --> 00:27:38,202
How so?

425
00:27:42,414 --> 00:27:45,702
What we have right now is good as it is.

426
00:27:46,964 --> 00:27:48,300
There’s no need to get married.

427
00:27:52,977 --> 00:27:56,800
Maybe marriage just isn’t
necessary for us.

428
00:28:01,750 --> 00:28:02,549
Pai.

429
00:28:05,210 --> 00:28:06,702
I’m going to be honest with you.

430
00:28:09,094 --> 00:28:10,656
I want to marry you.

431
00:28:14,041 --> 00:28:15,657
Why do you want to get married, baby?

432
00:28:26,520 --> 00:28:28,520
A COUNTER SO PAI CAN SIT
AND WATCH ME COOK.

433
00:28:28,531 --> 00:28:30,400
A HONEYMOON IN VENICE

434
00:28:32,080 --> 00:28:33,840
FOUR IDEAS FOR BATHROOM
PAI LOVES RELAXING BATHS.

435
00:28:35,540 --> 00:28:37,690
I originally planned it
for a gated community project.

436
00:28:37,712 --> 00:28:40,000
But as I kept going,
I began to want to have a house of my own.

437
00:28:40,022 --> 00:28:41,600
TIM AND PAI’S HOME PROJECT

438
00:28:43,183 --> 00:28:45,062
If you ask me why I want to get married,

439
00:28:45,282 --> 00:28:47,798
it’s probably because I want a house,

440
00:28:48,360 --> 00:28:50,201
somewhere more spacious,

441
00:28:50,546 --> 00:28:52,457
so we can start our own business.

442
00:28:53,510 --> 00:28:55,201
So I can take care of you
when you’re not well.

443
00:28:59,087 --> 00:29:00,099
And more importantly,

444
00:29:02,280 --> 00:29:04,602
I want to know
that you belong entirely to me.

445
00:29:10,282 --> 00:29:11,703
What if it turns out bad?

446
00:29:13,395 --> 00:29:14,819
Nothing’s perfect, Pai.

447
00:29:15,663 --> 00:29:18,897
But I promise to try my best.

448
00:29:21,720 --> 00:29:26,297
I really want you to know
how much getting married means to me.

449
00:29:30,235 --> 00:29:31,000
Well…

450
00:29:32,229 --> 00:29:33,900
Do you still have that ring?

451
00:29:39,590 --> 00:29:40,447
But…

452
00:29:44,190 --> 00:29:45,862
I bought this one.

453
00:29:49,720 --> 00:29:51,397
I didn’t want to buy it,

454
00:29:51,927 --> 00:29:54,497
but then I saw
how empty your ringfinger looks.

455
00:29:57,539 --> 00:29:58,197
Pai.

456
00:30:19,090 --> 00:30:20,297
Will you marry me?

457
00:31:33,229 --> 00:31:34,099
This way, please.

458
00:31:39,170 --> 00:31:41,891
Khao Yai isn’t as far as I thought.

459
00:31:41,920 --> 00:31:43,201
We got here in no time at all.

460
00:31:43,230 --> 00:31:46,699
Of course you’d say that.
You were sleeping the entire car ride.

461
00:31:47,602 --> 00:31:49,640
Please rest in your rooms for now.

462
00:31:49,669 --> 00:31:53,100
At 9 a.m. I will come get Mr. U
and Mr. North to the dressing room.

463
00:31:53,146 --> 00:31:54,583
The photoshoot starts at 11 o’clock.

464
00:31:54,611 --> 00:31:58,002
And we’ll start shooting
the presentation for the wedding at 1 p.m.

465
00:31:58,133 --> 00:31:59,398
-Yes.
-Yes.

466
00:32:00,770 --> 00:32:01,697
Beautiful, huh?

467
00:32:02,121 --> 00:32:03,000
This place?

468
00:32:03,419 --> 00:32:04,100
You.

469
00:32:04,200 --> 00:32:05,801
They’re flirting, U.

470
00:32:06,070 --> 00:32:07,197
We can do that later in our room.

471
00:32:11,130 --> 00:32:11,877
Hello.

472
00:32:12,417 --> 00:32:13,400
Hello, Grandpa.

473
00:32:15,005 --> 00:32:15,802
What?

474
00:32:16,090 --> 00:32:17,260
What are you looking at?

475
00:32:18,078 --> 00:32:20,251
We’re not here to bother you lot.

476
00:32:20,782 --> 00:32:23,259
We’re just here for a little getaway.

477
00:32:23,390 --> 00:32:26,896
Oh, and just go ahead and be at ease.

478
00:32:28,682 --> 00:32:30,000
If you are all ready,

479
00:32:30,205 --> 00:32:31,533
please follow me this way.

480
00:32:32,970 --> 00:32:33,696
Right.

481
00:32:36,213 --> 00:32:38,142
We’ll be so at ease here, Auntie.

482
00:32:41,380 --> 00:32:42,097
Pure.

483
00:32:42,659 --> 00:32:43,577
Pure!

484
00:32:44,103 --> 00:32:44,891
Come on!

485
00:32:44,930 --> 00:32:47,579
Sorry about that, Da Zhan.
My friend’s a little…

486
00:32:50,539 --> 00:32:51,647
You look handsome, U.

487
00:32:52,013 --> 00:32:53,100
Looks like a thug.

488
00:32:53,848 --> 00:32:55,100
Just like you, bro.

489
00:32:56,607 --> 00:32:58,995
Please turn to the other side.

490
00:33:00,480 --> 00:33:01,960
Chin up, please.

491
00:33:02,325 --> 00:33:03,462
Put on a big smile.

492
00:33:03,493 --> 00:33:04,254
U.

493
00:33:21,533 --> 00:33:22,302
North.

494
00:33:34,160 --> 00:33:35,678
Shall we begin?

495
00:33:37,232 --> 00:33:38,198
Like this?

496
00:33:39,340 --> 00:33:40,600
That's it.

497
00:33:45,590 --> 00:33:48,385
-That’s perfect.
-I’m so happy for him.

498
00:33:48,550 --> 00:33:50,103
I can’t help but be so proud of him.

499
00:33:59,800 --> 00:34:01,699
This place is so romantic,
don’t you think?

500
00:34:03,580 --> 00:34:04,598
It’s gorgeous.

501
00:34:04,780 --> 00:34:06,099
It’s totally romantic.

502
00:34:12,488 --> 00:34:13,202
U.

503
00:34:13,940 --> 00:34:15,397
I want to get married here,

504
00:34:15,961 --> 00:34:16,822
and now.

505
00:34:17,299 --> 00:34:17,976
Hmm?

506
00:34:18,327 --> 00:34:18,899
Hmm.

507
00:34:30,180 --> 00:34:30,951
Grandpa.

508
00:34:34,789 --> 00:34:35,930
I need to ask you something.

509
00:34:38,180 --> 00:34:40,096
Can I get married here today?

510
00:34:40,914 --> 00:34:41,395
What?

511
00:34:41,431 --> 00:34:42,502
Please, Grandpa?

512
00:34:43,580 --> 00:34:46,542
I want my wedding to be full
of everyone I love.

513
00:34:47,900 --> 00:34:49,902
I don’t want to get married
in front of strangers.

514
00:34:50,656 --> 00:34:52,699
I don’t want to fake another smile.

515
00:34:53,528 --> 00:34:54,278
But I think—

516
00:34:54,297 --> 00:34:56,395
All I ask is that
I get married here today.

517
00:34:56,988 --> 00:34:58,601
As for the wedding in Bangkok…

518
00:35:01,350 --> 00:35:03,697
I’ll agree to ‘perform’ it.

519
00:35:04,750 --> 00:35:07,402
I want my wedding to turn out amazing.

520
00:35:10,170 --> 00:35:11,400
You’re asking me that?

521
00:35:11,857 --> 00:35:12,500
Yes!

522
00:35:13,220 --> 00:35:14,017
Fine.

523
00:35:14,788 --> 00:35:17,397
I’ll allow it.

524
00:35:17,980 --> 00:35:19,094
Thank you, Grandpa!

525
00:35:19,149 --> 00:35:19,899
U!

526
00:35:20,826 --> 00:35:22,720
I’ll get right to it, sir.

527
00:35:22,838 --> 00:35:24,299
Please. Thank you.

528
00:35:28,022 --> 00:35:29,106
And you, Pai?

529
00:35:30,108 --> 00:35:32,600
Don’t you want to get married
here today, too?

530
00:35:38,370 --> 00:35:39,102
I do.

531
00:35:39,590 --> 00:35:41,002
I want to get married today, Grandpa.

532
00:35:45,622 --> 00:35:46,345
Oh, Pai.

533
00:35:48,120 --> 00:35:49,401
Let me hug him, too.

534
00:35:49,431 --> 00:35:50,431
Alright. Come on.

535
00:35:50,456 --> 00:35:51,696
Tim, let me hug Pai.

536
00:35:56,130 --> 00:35:57,945
I’m so happy.

537
00:35:58,850 --> 00:36:01,262
Can you please add more seats?

538
00:36:01,280 --> 00:36:03,198
The frame kind of looks empty right now.

539
00:36:03,240 --> 00:36:04,400
Of course, ma’am.

540
00:36:07,561 --> 00:36:08,997
Are these all the seats?

541
00:36:10,070 --> 00:36:11,746
Maybe you can try placing them first.

542
00:36:16,222 --> 00:36:16,980
Mr. Pai.

543
00:36:17,392 --> 00:36:21,798
I sent a chauffeur to fetch Mr. Prem,
Mr. Kuea, Ms. Oom, and your parents.

544
00:36:21,900 --> 00:36:23,210
They should be here soon.

545
00:36:24,035 --> 00:36:24,982
Thank you, Nana.

546
00:36:25,350 --> 00:36:26,096
Of course.

547
00:36:30,269 --> 00:36:30,980
Nana.

548
00:36:31,853 --> 00:36:32,600
Yes?

549
00:36:33,696 --> 00:36:36,397
Thank you for everything.

550
00:36:43,250 --> 00:36:44,202
Yes, sir.

551
00:36:44,955 --> 00:36:47,395
Excuse me.

552
00:36:58,340 --> 00:36:59,054
Tim.

553
00:37:01,910 --> 00:37:03,657
Let’s make this
the last time we get married.

554
00:37:06,804 --> 00:37:07,659
I promise.

555
00:37:11,980 --> 00:37:14,801
I need to thank all of you as well.

556
00:37:16,136 --> 00:37:20,220
Never in my life did I think
I’d ever have such a happy family.

557
00:37:21,811 --> 00:37:24,604
You all make me feel so belong.

558
00:37:26,410 --> 00:37:29,100
Please let me stay with you
for the rest of your lives,

559
00:37:29,290 --> 00:37:33,022
North, Tim, Pai.

560
00:37:40,250 --> 00:37:41,398
That was touching.

561
00:37:42,822 --> 00:37:43,502
But…

562
00:37:44,287 --> 00:37:48,497
I never thought
this day would come as well.

563
00:37:50,160 --> 00:37:52,202
We almost didn’t make it
so many times before.

564
00:37:53,610 --> 00:37:55,546
Thank you, both of you.

565
00:37:56,231 --> 00:37:57,202
And you as well, U.

566
00:37:58,310 --> 00:38:00,662
I’m happy we’re here today.

567
00:38:02,940 --> 00:38:03,997
I’m happy, too,

568
00:38:04,900 --> 00:38:07,401
that we got through everything.

569
00:38:08,540 --> 00:38:09,740
I love you all.

570
00:38:17,117 --> 00:38:17,871
My turn?

571
00:38:20,100 --> 00:38:22,200
I… don’t want to say anything.

572
00:38:22,862 --> 00:38:23,757
I might start crying.

573
00:38:24,710 --> 00:38:25,702
Come on, Tim.

574
00:38:27,554 --> 00:38:28,499
I love you all.

575
00:38:31,767 --> 00:38:32,456
Guys.

576
00:38:33,180 --> 00:38:35,450
I want to make a time capsule.

577
00:38:35,980 --> 00:38:38,700
But I don’t think burying it here
would be a good idea.

578
00:38:38,808 --> 00:38:41,702
We wouldn’t be able to dig it out
if they ever have to renovate the place.

579
00:38:42,310 --> 00:38:46,059
Shall we make a video instead
that we can take a look at in five years?

580
00:38:48,121 --> 00:38:48,702
Sure.

581
00:38:48,757 --> 00:38:52,072
Okay. I’ll start now.

582
00:38:56,280 --> 00:38:57,060
North,

583
00:38:58,070 --> 00:38:59,497
today is your wedding day.

584
00:38:59,854 --> 00:39:00,857
You made it.

585
00:39:01,825 --> 00:39:03,499
I wish you happiness.

586
00:39:03,659 --> 00:39:04,894
Love them all.

587
00:39:05,616 --> 00:39:07,604
Love U a lot.

588
00:39:08,188 --> 00:39:10,200
And love your big brothers, too.

589
00:39:11,410 --> 00:39:12,402
You’re amazing.

590
00:39:12,531 --> 00:39:13,401
You did it!

591
00:39:14,540 --> 00:39:15,798
U, your turn.

592
00:39:16,002 --> 00:39:16,602
Right.

593
00:39:17,557 --> 00:39:20,200
U, you’re not alone anymore.

594
00:39:20,630 --> 00:39:23,102
You have North, and a loving family.

595
00:39:23,228 --> 00:39:24,798
You have Tim and Pai.

596
00:39:25,131 --> 00:39:26,397
Make sure you love North right.

597
00:39:27,240 --> 00:39:28,002
Love you.

598
00:39:32,714 --> 00:39:34,200
Next…

599
00:39:35,161 --> 00:39:36,200
Let’s do it, Pai.

600
00:39:38,579 --> 00:39:39,800
What do I have to say?

601
00:39:41,770 --> 00:39:43,600
Whatever you want
to tell your future self.

602
00:40:41,210 --> 00:40:43,902
I, Thanin Chaiyanuwat,

603
00:40:44,930 --> 00:40:50,706
take Jirachote Jeeramongkolthanun
to be my lawfully wedded husband.

604
00:40:57,857 --> 00:41:01,100
I, Jirachote Jeeramongkolthanun,

605
00:41:02,470 --> 00:41:07,260
take Thanin Chaiyanuwat
to be my lawfully wedded husband.

606
00:41:09,340 --> 00:41:11,800
I, Issara Preechajit,

607
00:41:12,320 --> 00:41:17,801
take Nipitphon Jeeramongkolthanun
to be my lawfully wedded husband.

608
00:41:19,210 --> 00:41:22,801
I, Nipitphon Jeeramongkolthanun,

609
00:41:23,460 --> 00:41:28,460
take Issara Preechajit
to be my lawfully wedded husband.

610
00:42:05,510 --> 00:42:10,302
I swear to love and stay faithful to you

611
00:42:14,072 --> 00:42:15,200
for better

612
00:42:18,915 --> 00:42:19,739
or for worse.

613
00:42:19,830 --> 00:42:22,094
…And then we expand it.

614
00:42:22,520 --> 00:42:23,718
PRASIT PONGSANG
ONE HUNDRED AND TWENTY MILLION

615
00:42:23,754 --> 00:42:25,197
…for poorer,

616
00:42:27,980 --> 00:42:29,097
or richer,

617
00:42:30,360 --> 00:42:31,822
in sickness,

618
00:42:35,626 --> 00:42:36,800
and in health.

619
00:42:39,617 --> 00:42:40,454
To love…

620
00:42:40,900 --> 00:42:42,659
Here, too.

621
00:42:47,271 --> 00:42:48,510
…and cherish

622
00:42:50,160 --> 00:42:51,998
until death do us part.

623
00:43:43,450 --> 00:43:47,856
I pray your marriage is strong and long
like a mighty river.

624
00:43:49,297 --> 00:43:51,502
Put this in your home.

625
00:43:52,410 --> 00:43:53,939
Does it have to be a duck?

626
00:43:58,788 --> 00:43:59,997
You guys.

627
00:44:00,020 --> 00:44:01,798
Will you please come to the stairways?

628
00:44:01,930 --> 00:44:03,297
Let's go take some photos.

629
00:44:18,377 --> 00:44:19,001
Pai.

630
00:44:19,690 --> 00:44:21,000
I hope you’re happy.

631
00:44:21,835 --> 00:44:25,401
And I hope you know
everyone you have in your life loves you.

632
00:44:26,334 --> 00:44:29,531
Grandpa, Aunt Kia, Papa and Mama,

633
00:44:30,560 --> 00:44:32,739
Tim, North…

634
00:44:32,780 --> 00:44:34,802
What about me? Count me in.

635
00:44:36,700 --> 00:44:37,699
And U, of course.

636
00:44:38,140 --> 00:44:39,502
I hope you don’t take them for granted.

637
00:44:41,653 --> 00:44:43,702
Tim.

638
00:44:44,297 --> 00:44:45,600
It’s my turn now?

639
00:44:45,674 --> 00:44:46,308
Yeah.

640
00:44:47,715 --> 00:44:49,402
Tim.

641
00:44:50,571 --> 00:44:52,337
You gotta love Pai right.

642
00:44:53,330 --> 00:44:54,597
Take care of him.

643
00:44:55,139 --> 00:44:56,801
Take care of his family.

644
00:44:56,937 --> 00:44:58,854
And don’t forget to take care
of your own family.

645
00:44:59,097 --> 00:45:02,797
And most importantly,
don’t you dare hurt Pai again.

646
00:45:02,910 --> 00:45:03,697
You hear me?

647
00:45:04,140 --> 00:45:05,038
You hear me?

648
00:45:05,380 --> 00:45:06,496
Don’t hurt Pai again.

649
00:45:06,530 --> 00:45:09,001
-Come on here, you.
-Tim, careful.

650
00:45:13,760 --> 00:45:14,710
We’re on camera.
It’s okay.

651
00:45:15,710 --> 00:45:17,502
Get your fill of him as often as you can.

652
00:45:18,750 --> 00:45:20,102
-That’s enough.
-Keep going, Tim.

653
00:45:20,299 --> 00:45:21,370
-I said that’s enough.
-And I said keep going, Tim.

654
00:45:21,401 --> 00:45:22,697
We’re married, you know?

655
00:45:22,810 --> 00:45:24,020
-Baby!
-I can even do this.

656
00:45:24,051 --> 00:45:24,742
What?

657
00:45:25,385 --> 00:45:26,800
U, we can’t let them one up us.

658
00:45:26,890 --> 00:45:28,500
-Baby!
-U, come on!

